\cf1\f0\fs32 [Creating Your Own Translation File - template.txt]\cf2\par
\f1\fs22      If Elementary does not have a translation file already included for your language, it is easy to make your own.  First, open the file "...\\Skins\\Elementary\\@Resources\\Langauges\\template.txt" in Windows Notepad or another plain text editor.  The file should say "; LANGUAGE SUBSTITUTIONS" at the top and have a lists of English words followed by "=" signs.  Simply put, whatever word you fill in after the "=" sign will replace the English word in the skin.  So just fill in the list, putting the word in your language after the "=".  (For examples, you can look at the other files in the "...\\@Resources\\Languages\\" folder.)\par
     When you're done, simply save the file with a new name ("Save as...").  You can call the file whatever you want, but keep it in the "...\\@Resources\\Languages\\" folder.  Then, in the Settings.txt file, simply change the "langauge" value to whatever you named your new translations file.  (If you named your file "MyLanguage.txt", in Settings.txt the Key=Value would be "language=MyLanguage".)\par
     That's it!  If you would like your new translations file included in the Elementary skin package, just contact me on DeviantArt or by email (see below).\par
